# Architecture And Routing Guardrails

- Keep the current routing model based on `currentPage` state and `navigateTo(page)` in `App.jsx`.
- Do not introduce React Router or alternate routing frameworks unless explicitly requested by the user.
- Preserve lazy loading with `React.lazy()` and `Suspense` for page-level components.
- Maintain existing page identifiers and navigation flow unless a task explicitly requires changing them.
- Prefer focused component-level refactors over broad architectural rewrites.
- Do not alter core business logic while performing UI or layout tasks.
